columns.comment: Point figure is a change quantity used in price indices, which expresses the price, average price or index of the reference period relative to the price, average price or index of the base period. The point figure of the base period is usually denoted by the number hundred. For example, if the point figure of the commodity is 105.3 in a certain period, it means that the price of the commodity has risen by 5.3 per cent from the base period.
